        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:14PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Wolf Creek Park, or 13 miles northwest of Canadian,
moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glazier and Wolf Creek Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
